1: O God, hurry to take me out of trouble. O Lord, hurry to help me!
2: Let those who want to kill me be ashamed and brought low. Let those who want to hurt me be turned away in shame.
3: Let those who say, “O, O!” be turned back because of their shame.
4: Let all who look for You be full of joy and be glad in You. And let those who love Your saving power always say, “Let God be honored.”
5: But I am poor and in need. Hurry to me, O God! You are my help and the One Who takes me out of trouble. O Lord, do not wait.
